The paper discusses the concept of explainability in AI systems, which is a key topic in the field of AI (cs.AI). It also touches upon the psychological theories of explanation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the history of computer science efforts to create intelligent tutoring systems and expert systems, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper highlights the need for researchers to provide fuller details on their empirical or experimental methods, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
